title: Injectable Contraceptive ICD10CM Surveillance
purpose: (Clinical Focus: Family Planning - provision and use of most and moderately effective contraceptive methods),(Data Element Scope: Diagnosis codes indicating surveillance of injectable contraceptive, a moderately effective method of contraception),(Inclusion Criteria: Diagnosis codes indicating surveillance of injectable contraceptive, a moderately effective method of contraception),(Exclusion Criteria: Any contraceptive method that is not injectable; Most effective (i.e., sterilization, intrauterine devices or systems (IUDs or IUDs) contraceptive implants) or moderately effective (i.e., oral pills, patch, or ring) methods of contraception; Less effective methods of contraception (i.e., diaphragm, male condom, female condom, withdrawal, sponge, fertility-awareness based methods, spermicide))
